cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SY 

The paper deals with game theory and algorithmic synthesis of strategies, which are topics that fall under cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the study of undecidability, which is a topic in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The use of graphs and finite-state strategies suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
